23// Performs constant folding and strength reduction on nodes that have
24// machine operators.
25class V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE MachineOperatorReducer final
26 : public NON_EXPORTED_BASE(AdvancedReducer) {
27 public:
28 enum SignallingNanPropagation {
29 kSilenceSignallingNan,
30 kPropagateSignallingNan
31 };
32
33 explicit MachineOperatorReducer(
34 Editor* editor, MachineGraph* mcgraph,
35 SignallingNanPropagation signalling_nan_propagation);
36 ~MachineOperatorReducer() override;
37
38 const char* reducer_name() const override { return "MachineOperatorReducer"; }
39
40 Reduction Reduce(Node* node) override;
41
42 private:
43 friend class Word32Adapter;
44 friend class Word64Adapter;
45
46 Node* Float32Constant(float value);
47 Node* Float64Constant(double value);
48 Node* Int32Constant(int32_t value);
49 Node* Int64Constant(int64_t value);
50 Node* Uint32Constant(uint32_t value) {
51 return Int32Constant(base::bit_cast<int32_t>(value));
52 }
53 Node* Uint64Constant(uint64_t value) {
54 return Int64Constant(base::bit_cast<int64_t>(value));
55 }
56 Node* Float64Mul(Node* lhs, Node* rhs);
57 Node* Float64PowHalf(Node* value);
58 Node* Word32And(Node* lhs, Node* rhs);
59 Node* Word32And(Node* lhs, uint32_t rhs) {
60 return Word32And(lhs, Uint32Constant(rhs));
61 }
62 Node* Word32Sar(Node* lhs, uint32_t rhs);
63 Node* Word64Sar(Node* lhs, uint32_t rhs);
64 Node* Word32Shr(Node* lhs, uint32_t rhs);
65 Node* Word64Shr(Node* lhs, uint32_t rhs);
66 Node* Word32Equal(Node* lhs, Node* rhs);
67 Node* Word64Equal(Node* lhs, Node* rhs);
68 Node* Word64And(Node* lhs, Node* rhs);
69 Node* Word64And(Node* lhs, uint64_t rhs) {
70 return Word64And(lhs, Uint64Constant(rhs));
71 }
72 Node* Int32Add(Node* lhs, Node* rhs);
73 Node* Int64Add(Node* lhs, Node* rhs);
74 Node* Int32Sub(Node* lhs, Node* rhs);
75 Node* Int64Sub(Node* lhs, Node* rhs);
76 Node* Int32Mul(Node* lhs, Node* rhs);
77 Node* Int64Mul(Node* lhs, Node* rhs);
78 Node* Int32Div(Node* dividend, int32_t divisor);
79 Node* Int64Div(Node* dividend, int64_t divisor);
80 Node* Uint32Div(Node* dividend, uint32_t divisor);
81 Node* Uint64Div(Node* dividend, uint64_t divisor);
82 Node* TruncateInt64ToInt32(Node* value);
83 Node* ChangeInt32ToInt64(Node* value);
84
85 Reduction ReplaceBool(bool value) { return ReplaceInt32(value ? 1 : 0); }
86 Reduction ReplaceFloat32(float value) {
87 return Replace(Float32Constant(value));
88 }
89 Reduction ReplaceFloat64(double value) {
90 return Replace(Float64Constant(value));
91 }
92 Reduction ReplaceInt32(int32_t value) {
93 return Replace(Int32Constant(value));
94 }
95 Reduction ReplaceUint32(uint32_t value) {
96 return Replace(Uint32Constant(value));
97 }
98 Reduction ReplaceInt64(int64_t value) {
99 return Replace(Int64Constant(value));
100 }
101 Reduction ReplaceUint64(uint64_t value) {
102 return Replace(Uint64Constant(value));
103 }

151 // These reductions can be applied to operations of different word sizes.
152 // Use Word32Adapter or Word64Adapter to specialize for a particular one.
153 template <typename WordNAdapter>
154 Reduction ReduceWordNAnd(Node* node);
155 template <typename WordNAdapter>
156 Reduction ReduceWordNOr(Node* node);
157 template <typename WordNAdapter>
158 Reduction ReduceWordNXor(Node* node);
159 template <typename WordNAdapter>
160 Reduction ReduceUintNLessThanOrEqual(Node* node);
161
162 // Tries to simplify "if(x == 0)" by removing the "== 0" and inverting
163 // branches.
164 Reduction SimplifyBranch(Node* node);
165 // Helper for SimplifyBranch; swaps the if/else of a branch.
166 void SwapBranches(Node* node);
167
168 // Helper for ReduceConditional. Does not perform the actual reduction; just
169 // returns a new Node that could be used as the input to the condition.
170 template <typename WordNAdapter>
171 base::Optional<Node*> ReduceConditionalN(Node* node);
172
173 // Helper for finding a reduced equality condition. Does not perform the
174 // actual reduction; just returns a new pair that could be compared for the
175 // same outcome. uintN_t corresponds to the size of the Equal operator, and
176 // thus the size of rhs. While the size of the WordNAdaptor corresponds to the
177 // size of lhs, with the sizes being different for
178 // Word32Equal(TruncateInt64ToInt32(lhs), rhs).
179 template <typename WordNAdapter, typename uintN_t,
180 typename intN_t = typename std::make_signed<uintN_t>::type>
181 base::Optional<std::pair<Node*, uintN_t>> ReduceWordEqualForConstantRhs(
182 Node* lhs, uintN_t rhs);
183
184 MachineGraph* mcgraph_;
185 SignallingNanPropagation signalling_nan_propagation_;
186};
